Then one, that was hardier than another, demanded of him the cause of his laughingâ€š and then he told to him how the Danes had assembled in great power of people against the realm of England, and were entering into their shipsj and as the king of Denmark would have entered into the ship, suddenly his strength was taken from him, and so fell into the sea between two ships and was drowned, by whose death the people of Denmark, and also of England, were delivered from sin and peril. They, hearing this, marvelled greatly, and sent into Den- mark to know the truth. And when the messengers returned, they reported that it was true as the king had said, and that the king of Denmark was drowned that same time that S. Edward laughed.
